when you finally re-experience
everything

13:07.583 --> 13:10.500
and that spark of wonder
in your eyes goes dark again.

13:10.500 --> 13:12.041
Oh, jeez.

13:12.041 --> 13:16.041
This is what I needed, you guys.
Just a night with my closest,

13:16.041 --> 13:17.834
closest girlfriends.

13:17.834 --> 13:21.083
[Regina] ♪ I learned how to
carry on And now you're back ♪

13:21.083 --> 13:23.583
- Who wants more wine?
- And your mother.

13:23.583 --> 13:26.583
Andrea, you know you don't
have to finish every bottle.

13:26.583 --> 13:30.083
It's not Cracker Jacks.
There's no prize in the bottom.

13:30.083 --> 13:32.959
The prize is the more I drink,
the blurrier you get.

13:32.959 --> 13:35.750
- To Sam.
- [all] To Sam!

13:35.750 --> 13:37.875
To forgetting
that son of a bitch.

13:37.875 --> 13:39.041
Yeah, to hell with him.

13:39.041 --> 13:41.500
Yeah,
he was a son of a bitch.

13:41.500 --> 13:45.250
Don't say that about him. Why
would you say that about him?

13:46.291 --> 13:48.041
I think
I heard it somewhere.

13:48.041 --> 13:50.125
Kevin was a kind
and thoughtful man.

13:50.125 --> 13:53.125
- He was so sweet.
- He was an ass.

13:53.125 --> 13:56.250
I'm confused
about my role here.

13:56.250 --> 14:00.333
I had such big plans
for them.

14:00.333 --> 14:03.041
The two of them were going
to buy a second house

14:03.041 --> 14:05.041
in Asheville, North Carolina.

14:05.041 --> 14:09.959
Not Boca Raton. It's way too
humid, you know, my hair would
never do...

14:09.959 --> 14:13.375
And Asheville has this

14:13.375 --> 14:16.250
thriving mountain
crafts community.

14:16.250 --> 14:17.792
Oh, God.

14:17.792 --> 14:21.834
That was my own fault. I
completely misjudged that Kevin.

14:21.834 --> 14:24.667
I thought he could handle
a girl with head problems.

14:24.667 --> 14:28.041
Mom, it's not your fault, OK?
It's not.

14:28.041 --> 14:30.041
It's my fault.
You know why?

14:31.375 --> 14:34.041
Because I'm unlovable.
[sobbing]

14:34.041 --> 14:36.041
You are not unlovable.

14:36.041 --> 14:38.208
Oh, honey, no, no.

14:38.208 --> 14:42.000
I mean true, there were times
you were difficult to warm up
to,

14:42.000 --> 14:44.250
but even then, I loved you.

14:45.583 --> 14:47.041
Babies are hard.

14:47.041 --> 14:48.583
I love you, too, Sam.

14:48.583 --> 14:51.709
And what about Todd?
Todd loved you. Hmm?

14:55.542 --> 15:00.458
Todd!

15:00.458 --> 15:05.041
- Todd!
- It might interest you to know

15:05.041 --> 15:08.000
this isn't even close
to the most embarrassing thing

15:08.000 --> 15:10.041
I've seen you do
on this sidewalk.

15:10.041 --> 15:12.291
Shh. Todd!

15:12.291 --> 15:15.500
- May I ask
why you're doing this?
- I want Todd.

15:15.500 --> 15:18.917
"Who" is no longer a secret to
anyone on this side of the lake.

15:18.917 --> 15:20.417
I was wondering why.

15:22.083 --> 15:26.542
'Cause I need to know
if he really loved me. OK?

15:26.542 --> 15:28.458
Todd!

15:28.458 --> 15:30.834
Come on.
Come on. Come on.

15:30.834 --> 15:33.041
- Let's get some coffee in you.
- Todd!

15:33.041 --> 15:34.458
OK.

15:34.458 --> 15:37.583
Oh! Good news, Frank. I don't
have a drinking problem anymore.

15:39.041 --> 15:42.041
- Gee, oopsie-daisy.
- No. Now it's mine.

15:45.667 --> 15:48.917
Ooh...
Drinking is like love.

15:48.917 --> 15:51.083
It starts out OK.

15:51.083 --> 15:54.041
The singing and
the laughing part is real fun,

15:54.041 --> 15:59.333
and then it just takes this ugly
turn around the crying and the
yelling part.

15:59.333 --> 16:01.709
I would tell you
about the throwing up part,

16:01.709 --> 16:03.959
but I don't want
to ruin the surprise.

16:05.166 --> 16:06.709
That is it.

16:07.709 --> 16:11.834
I am never falling
in love again.

16:11.834 --> 16:14.542
Of course you will.

16:14.542 --> 16:18.667
And it may hurt.
But you will survive.

16:18.667 --> 16:20.667
Oh, my God!

16:20.667 --> 16:22.750
You speak the words
of Gloria!

16:22.750 --> 16:25.333
My wife and I karaoke.

16:25.333 --> 16:27.125
She does an excellent Devo.

16:27.125 --> 16:29.250
You are so lucky.

16:29.250 --> 16:31.709
You have a wife.

16:31.709 --> 16:33.667
I bet you she has a drawer.

16:33.667 --> 16:35.834
She has all the drawers.

16:35.834 --> 16:40.667
Yeah, but she loves you.
Someone loves you.

16:41.458 --> 16:43.500
How great is that?

16:43.500 --> 16:45.083
Someone once said,

16:45.083 --> 16:49.291
"The joy in life is not in
hearing the words 'I love you,'

16:49.291 --> 16:51.959
but in being lucky enough
to say them."

16:51.959 --> 16:54.959
Wow, that's beautiful.

16:54.959 --> 16:58.583
- Who said that?
- The lead character
in my screenplay.

16:58.583 --> 17:01.667
It happens just before
the shark gets him.

17:01.667 --> 17:03.250
And he was right.

17:03.250 --> 17:07.417
I mean, some people never do let
themselves express their love.

17:07.417 --> 17:11.125
How can you not express it,
you know?

17:11.125 --> 17:14.667
Like who can't express love?

17:16.083 --> 17:17.667
Wait.

17:18.500 --> 17:19.667
Wait.

17:20.417 --> 17:21.667
Wait.

17:22.667 --> 17:24.417
- Hey, Sam?
- Uh-huh.

17:24.417 --> 17:26.834
- Are we living together?
- [chuckles]

17:26.834 --> 17:29.792
- Don't be an idiot.
- Well, I mean I'm here
all the time,

17:29.792 --> 17:32.667
I've got a drawer,
I've got a third of the closet.

17:32.667 --> 17:36.667
No, we are not living together
because that would imply

17:36.667 --> 17:40.166
that you would be paying
half of the mortgage. And I...

17:40.166 --> 17:41.709
...don't see that happening.

17:41.709 --> 17:45.375
Yeah, I don't either.
Yeah, but I can still
hang out here, right?

17:45.375 --> 17:47.834
Eat what's in the fridge,
sleep in your bed?

17:47.834 --> 17:50.834
If you stopped,
I'd kill you.

17:50.834 --> 17:52.375
I love you, too.

17:57.667 --> 18:00.417
Did I not say it to Todd?

18:00.417 --> 18:02.500
Maybe I didn't.

18:02.500 --> 18:05.333
Maybe I never even told him
that I loved him.

18:07.000 --> 18:08.250
Todd!

18:10.458 --> 18:12.250
What? What's going on?

18:12.250 --> 18:14.083
Did I ever tell you
that I loved you?

18:14.083 --> 18:16.291
- Wait, I'm sorry?
- Did I?

18:16.291 --> 18:17.959
Out loud? No.

18:17.959 --> 18:20.792
Well, you scratched it
into the trunk of my car once.

18:20.792 --> 18:23.542
- It was OK, it was an old car.
- Well, I did.

18:23.542 --> 18:26.458
- What?
- I loved you.

18:26.458 --> 18:28.709
I'm sorry that I didn't
tell you before, OK?

18:28.709 --> 18:31.500
But I'm pretty sure
that I did.

18:31.500 --> 18:35.000
I mean then.
Not now. Before.

18:35.000 --> 18:39.166
All right, let's just pretend
like it's a long time ago, OK?

18:39.166 --> 18:41.375
Just, ready?

18:41.375 --> 18:43.667
I love you!

18:43.667 --> 18:46.667
Then. Because not now.

18:47.583 --> 18:49.250
FYI.

18:49.250 --> 18:51.709
- OK, then.
- You bet.

18:53.417 --> 18:55.250
[mumbles indistinctly]

19:08.125 --> 19:09.667
Todd...

19:10.667 --> 19:12.000
...I love you!

19:12.000 --> 19:13.959
Shut up, Russ.

19:18.625 --> 19:21.083
Well, I expressed it.

19:21.083 --> 19:24.041
- I expressed the hell
out of it.
- It went well, then.

19:24.041 --> 19:27.667
Yeah. Yeah.
In fact, from now on,

19:27.667 --> 19:30.083
I'm only going to say
"I love you" to guys

19:30.083 --> 19:33.083
after I don't
love them anymore.

19:33.083 --> 19:34.959
Because it goes
so much better.

19:34.959 --> 19:38.041
- Sounds like a plan.
- Yep.

19:39.667 --> 19:41.750
OK, except for this once.

19:43.166 --> 19:44.667
- Frank...
- Don't you dare.

19:44.667 --> 19:46.291
I wasn't. Really.

19:53.250 --> 19:56.917
[Samantha] So love
really is a battlefield.

19:56.917 --> 20:00.542
I learned that from another
prophet on that CD at Andrea's.

20:02.667 --> 20:04.875
The difference is,
in battle,

20:04.875 --> 20:08.834
you're supposed to shoot all
your ammo at once and
annihilate the other side.

20:08.834 --> 20:12.709
In love, sometimes you just got
to hold your fire a little

20:12.709 --> 20:14.208
and see what happens.

20:14.208 --> 20:17.417
Tracy, grab me that file on the
Woodcrest property, please?

20:17.417 --> 20:19.208
In a minute, sweetie,
I got to dry.

20:19.208 --> 20:21.792
At least I know
I can express myself now.

20:21.792 --> 20:24.417
You know what, Tracy?

20:24.417 --> 20:29.000
I'm not sure if this whole
girlfriend thing is working out
so well.

20:29.000 --> 20:33.583
- It works for me.
- No, you work for me.

20:33.583 --> 20:37.000
I am your boss
and you are my assistant,

20:37.000 --> 20:39.667
which means that you have
my Tanzania Peaberry

20:39.667 --> 20:41.667
on my desk when I get here
in the morning

20:41.667 --> 20:43.792
and keep your ass
in that chair at night

20:43.792 --> 20:46.291
until you're sure
I'm at home in my jammies.

20:46.291 --> 20:49.875
- Are we clear, girlfriend?
- Yes, Miss Newly.

20:55.291 --> 20:59.709
[Samantha] Maybe the key
to survival in love and war
is balance.

20:59.709 --> 21:02.917
Did I say please?
I'm sorry, please.

21:02.917 --> 21:04.667
And thank you.

21:04.667 --> 21:06.667
Now get back to work!

21:06.667 --> 21:10.041
- Please. Right now!
- Oh...

21:10.041 --> 21:11.917
Thank you.

21:11.917 --> 21:12.917
Please.
